01:05:21.780 --> 01:05:26.720
would be interesting to do that. You've given
me an idea just now, so what we'll have to

01:05:26.720 --> 01:05:31.890
include you as a co-author if we do a million-dollar
bill experiment. I think there may be something

01:05:31.890 --> 01:05:37.250
to what you're saying and I have to say in
honesty, I used it in part for the humor value,

01:05:37.250 --> 01:05:42.770
but you can easily find lists of all these
stupid -- Google stupid crimes and you'll

01:05:42.770 --> 01:05:47.920
get a lot of them. And I can't help but think
that one thing that's going on in these cases

01:05:47.920 --> 01:05:50.839
is that the criminals think they're better
at crime than they really are. Now, there

01:05:50.839 --> 01:05:53.790
are probably other things happening, too,
like "where did this guy get the million-dollar

01:05:53.790 --> 01:05:56.880
bill and how did he think he came into it
without paying for it with a million dollars"

01:05:56.880 --> 01:06:00.460
or something like that. So, there's obviously
more to the story and maybe you're right about

01:06:00.460 --> 01:06:02.900
that he was just trying to really like, wow
them with even more confidence.

01:06:02.900 --> 01:06:04.539
&gt;&gt;audience #10: Yeah, I don't know.

01:06:04.539 --> 01:06:05.640
&gt;&gt;Chris Chabris: Could be.

01:06:05.640 --> 01:06:07.020
&gt;&gt;audience #10: Thinking about it.

