01:06:18.960 --> 01:06:21.200
onto things we carry, like cell phones.

01:06:21.200 --> 01:06:22.200
&gt;&gt;Chris Chabris: Mm-hmm.

01:06:22.200 --> 01:06:25.510
&gt;&gt;audience #11: Like, ten years ago, if you
ask someone to give, speak out the five closest

01:06:25.510 --> 01:06:27.450
people's phone numbers, they could do that.

01:06:27.450 --> 01:06:28.450
&gt;&gt;Chris Chabris: Right.

01:06:28.450 --> 01:06:30.230
&gt;&gt;audience #11: Today, I don't think anyone
would be able to cite those numbers.

01:06:30.230 --> 01:06:31.230
&gt;&gt;Chris Chabris: Right.

01:06:31.230 --> 01:06:34.130
&gt;&gt;audience #11: So, it's all just [ ] cognition,
so do we really need to make a distinction

01:06:34.130 --> 01:06:35.710
between what's in the head versus what's with
me?

01:06:35.710 --> 01:06:40.319
&gt;&gt;Chris Chabris: Right, so this is an excellent
question. What is this boundary between the

01:06:40.319 --> 01:06:48.589
head and this boundary right here that's made
up of bone and skin and so on. Is that really

01:06:48.589 --> 01:06:51.089
cognitively significant anymore, as significant
as it used to be? And I think the answer is

01:06:51.089 --> 01:06:57.460
no. To some, it's not as, it's not completely
unimportant, it's not irrelevant, but it's

01:06:57.460 --> 01:07:03.310
not as important for the reason you say. And
maybe we should start to, instead of studying

01:07:03.310 --> 01:07:06.640
the individual, abilities of the individual
as much as we did, which is the traditional

01:07:06.640 --> 01:07:09.809
way in cognitive psychology and cognitive
neuroscience, start to study the abilities

01:07:09.809 --> 01:07:15.250
of the human computer or the human device
partnership, or the human Internet partnership

01:07:15.250 --> 01:07:21.000
or of groups of people working together which
increasingly happens in workplaces much more

01:07:21.000 --> 01:07:24.940
than it used to. And I actually, I started
doing a little bit of research on that myself

01:07:24.940 --> 01:07:28.319
where I did something really trivial. I had
people do an IQ test, not an IQ test, sorry.

01:07:28.319 --> 01:07:34.099
I had them do a GRE, a standardized test with
or without a computer that they had access

01:07:34.099 --> 01:07:37.319
to just for fun to see what would happen and
how much smarter do they get when they have

01:07:37.319 --> 01:07:44.000
a computer. And it turns out, good news. They
do better. But maybe not, maybe not as much

01:07:44.000 --> 01:07:47.410
better as you might think and it might differ
depending on what kind of materials they are

01:07:47.410 --> 01:07:52.289
and so on. And so I think we, that's a very
faint first step at starting to study exactly

01:07:52.289 --> 01:07:56.250
the phenomenon you're talking about and move
that into what psychologists study when they

01:07:56.250 --> 01:08:01.240
study intelligence and human abilities and
so on. It's a good suggestion.

