01:08:26.950 --> 01:08:31.450
no. We haven't done that and part of the reason
for that is that it's a methodological challenge

01:08:31.450 --> 01:08:35.890
to repeat these experiences enough times that
you can get enough data to really answer those

01:08:35.890 --> 01:08:39.980
questions. Once people know there's a gorilla
coming, it's hard to redo the same thing again.

01:08:39.980 --> 01:08:42.771
There has been research on what goes on in
the brain when we pay attention to one thing

01:08:42.771 --> 01:08:47.390
and ignore other things, but we haven't, that's
not stuff that we've actually done ourselves.

01:08:47.390 --> 01:08:48.390
Thanks.

